280
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:57,400
-Jiw, what would you like?
-Can I have you?

281
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:58,800
You little brat.

282
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,040
-Sis.
-What is it?

283
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,880
Can I get the song "Melon Garden Girl"?

284
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:06,280
-Bring the bananas.
-Got it, kid.

285
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:23,000
Melon garden girl of Suphan.

286
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:29,240
Talked about all over the city.

287
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,920
(Jane)
I’m in Thailand now.

288
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,360
See you tomorrow.

289
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,800
Is something wrong?

290
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:52,520
Oh.

291
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,520
Well...

292
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,040
I think

293
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,280
I might have to go home tonight.

294
00:18:58,560 --> 00:19:00,840
I have something urgent to take care of.

295
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:02,280
And

296
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,680
tomorrow I plan to go to the office

297
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,200
to discuss the project
we talked about today.

298
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,560
Are you hiding something from me?

299
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,920
You’re not good at lying.

300
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:19,400
Your face gives it away, you know?

301
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,160
Oh.

302
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:29,160
Well...

303
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,240
There’s something

304
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:33,920
really important I need to settle first.

305
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:38,120
Once I get everything sorted,

306
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,360
I’ll tell you everything.

307
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,160
I’m not trying to pressure you,

308
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,320
but that thing you mentioned,

309
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,760
is it about...

310
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,760
someone else?

311
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,480
Come on, you.

312
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:00,000
It’s nothing.

313
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,480
You promised you wouldn’t cheat on me.

314
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,520
I won’t betray you either.

315
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,440
I trust you.

316
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:17,120
I actually want to drive you,

317
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:18,800
but I’m not good at driving at night.

318
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:22,280
I’ve got a bit of trauma.

319
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,000
Trauma?

320
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,600
About what?

321
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,320
My parents.

322
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:30,000
They used to fight when I was little.

323
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,400
So they drove fast out of spite.

324
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,880
And I was sitting in the back that day.

325
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:38,800
In the end, there was an accident.

326
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,080
And I was the only one who survived.

327
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,760
That must have been really hard for you.

328
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,440
It’s okay.

329
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:52,480
Today, I promise

330
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,480
I’ll drive slowly

331
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,960
and carefully.

332
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,320
And I’ll call you as soon as I arrive.

333
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:00,440
Don’t worry.

334
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,720
Mm.

335
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,320
I’m heading out now.

336
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,480
Go on.

337
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:45,680
You’ll come back, right?

338
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,200
Of course.

339
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,520
Where else could someone like me go?

340
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,480
It’s been a while.

341
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,720
How have you been?

342
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:13,840
Are you doing well?

343
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,680
Do I look sick to you?

344
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:26,160
I missed you.

345
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:27,200
Excuse me.

346
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:35,680
Si.

347
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,640
Say something to me.

348
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:39,920
Anything.

349
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,480
If you have something to say, just say it.

350
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,240
I don’t have much time.

351
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:51,680
I just got back to Thailand.

352
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:55,200
I just wanted to see my girlfriend.

353
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,840
Do people in a relationship
need a reason to meet?

354
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,240
Coconut water, please.

355
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,960
Si.

356
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:14,040
Si.

357
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:16,120
I’m sorry.

358
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,800
I’m sorry for not replying to your messages.

359
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,680
I’m sorry for not answering your calls.

360
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:23,440
But things over there were really busy.

361
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:26,920
And you know our time zones are different.

362
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,160
I came to see you, didn’t I?

363
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,200
Where are you going?

364
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,320
To the restroom.

365
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:44,200
What’s wrong with her?

366
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,840
Excuse me, serving.

367
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,080
I’m sorry.

368
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,960
It’s okay, I’ll clean it up myself.

369
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,040
Do you want anything else?

370
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,400
I’ll order it for you.

371
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:44,080
Want some?

372
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:12,280
Si.

373
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,120
Do you want anything else?

374
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,320
So,

375
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,720
you don’t have anything to say, right?

376
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:20,760
Then...

377
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:22,080
I’m leaving.

378
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:25,120
Si.

379
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:31,720
Damn it, I really messed up.

380
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,640
I should’ve replied to her messages.

381
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,280
Then I could’ve kept her around.

382
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:44,880
Consider it compensation
for my wasted time, Si.

383
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:53,280
Go on, what is it, my child?

384
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:56,920
I have a new project
with the villagers in Suphan Buri.

385
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,440
to present to you.

386
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,720
You might not be interested right now,

387
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:13,400
but I think this project is interesting.

388
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,000
If you agree,

389
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:16,680
Klao will reduce

390
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,840
the land rent for S Mall.

391
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:22,400
And you can develop the marketing plan as CHR

392
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,160
to support Thai farmers.

393
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:25,680
This deal

394
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:27,480
is a win-win, Dad.

395
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,240
Dad, P’Si,

396
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,840
is something going on?

397
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,400
I just brought a project to present.

398
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:40,120
I’m not here to take your CEO position.

399
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,320
Don’t worry.

400
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,120
I’m leaving now, Dad.

401
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:45,400
If

402
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,760
you’re interested,

403
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,120
just let me know.

404
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:52,680
Your sister brought me a project.

405
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,080
I think it’s quite interesting.

406
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:56,040
You can take over and handle it.

407
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:58,080
As soon as possible, my child.

408
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,520
Yes!

409
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:35,680
Why are you so late?

410
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:36,720
What?

411
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:38,200
Weren’t you the one who told me

412
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:40,400
to drive slowly and safely?

413
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,000
So why are you complaining now?

414
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,560
Sorry, but...

415
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,320
I don’t want to keep them waiting.

416
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:47,960
So how are we getting there?

417
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,880
Tada.

418
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,800
You bought a new motorcycle?

419
00:27:58,920 --> 00:27:59,920
Nice.

420
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:02,200
Now I don’t have to deal with messy hair

421
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,080
because of that “old uncle” anymore.

422
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,000
So, can we go now?

423
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,320
Yeah, let’s go.

424
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,040
Wait, let me change first.

425
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,440
This outfit doesn’t really fit with the uncles and aunties.

426
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,320
I already prepared something for you.

427
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:16,080
Here.

428
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:19,560
Wow, really?

429
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:21,920
How could I be slow with something like this?

430
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,080
Give it to me.

431
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:25,000
Hey, you.

432
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,120
You’re changing right here?

433
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:27,880
-Why?
-Aren’t you embarrassed?

434
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:29,160
Embarrassed of what?

435
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:31,200
Weren’t you the one who said

436
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:32,680
we’re both women,

437
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,120
so why be shy?

438
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:47,040
All done.

439
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:48,280
Let’s go.

440
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:51,400
Here, I’ll put it on for you.

441
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,360
-Let’s go.
-Let’s go.

442
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,200
Alright, let’s go.

443
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:14,040
-Hello, hello, kid, hello.
-Okay.

444
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,480
-So drunk.
-Hey.

445
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:17,760
They’re here.

446
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:19,520
Come on.

447
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,000
Klao, look.

448
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,960
-Hello, Uncle Headman.
-Hello, kid, hello.

449
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:26,280
Sorry I’m late.

450
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:27,840
I had a work discussion in Bangkok.

451
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,960
That’s alright, kid, it’s alright.

452
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,920
Si also said

453
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,240
that the mall executives

454
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:35,080
have approved our business plan.

455
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:36,680
Wow, that’s great.

456
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,800
Today, the uncles

457
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:40,680
prepared lots of food.

458
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:42,080
Let’s go share the good news

459
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:43,600
and celebrate together, kid. Let’s go.

460
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:45,000
-Sure.
-Let’s go, kid.

461
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:47,000
Alright, everyone.

462
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,160
This is Si.

463
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,960
-Hello.
-She’s from Bangkok.

464
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:52,600
She’s going to be our village’s
new daughter-in-law.

465
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:54,560
She’s pretty.

466
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:56,120
She really is.

467
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,080
Klao is all smiles.

468
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:01,120
I’ll take care of you myself.

469
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,760
Have a seat, boss.

470
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:05,800
You’re number one to me.

471
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,160
Yes, thank you. Hello.

472
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:11,160
Yes?

473
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:16,160
You brat.

474
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,880
Cheers.

475
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:27,000
Sis, is she your wife?

476
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:29,440
She’s really pretty.

477
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:30,960
Cheers.

478
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,480
-Finish it, sis.
-Yeah.

479
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:37,840
Hey, hey.

480
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:38,920
You.

481
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:42,560
She’s jealous of you.

482
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:46,240
Chill.

483
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:47,520
What do you mean chill?

484
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:51,960
Parrot lady, don’t interrupt my sister.

485
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,160
She’s just getting tipsy.

486
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:56,360
Let it slide, just a little.

487
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,840
You too.

488
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,920
You’re still young, why are you drinking?

489
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:03,480
If your sister gets too drunk to ride home,

490
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:06,040
then you carry her back yourself.

491
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:08,480
What are you talking about?

492
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,920
Whoever’s girlfriend she is can take care of her.

493
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:13,040
So sweet.

494
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:14,200
She’s the boss.

495
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,440
-Si.
-Yes, Uncle Headman?

496
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,000
Come here, kid.

497
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,400
Come on.

498
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:23,920
This way.

499
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:25,920
It’s starting.

500
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,360
I’m here.

501
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:30,760
More, more.

502
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:34,120
Wow, my sister is number one in Suphan.

503
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:35,760
Strong drinker.

504
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,680
-Strong drinker.
-Strong.

505
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:41,400
You’re intense.

506
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:43,680
So intense.

507
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:45,040
Totally wild.

508
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:46,440
You even said

509
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:48,000
you’re that intense.

510
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:54,960
Everyone

511
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:57,280
wants to tie a string on your wrist

512
00:31:57,280 --> 00:32:00,240
to welcome the new
daughter-in-law of our village.

513
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:04,200
-I’m not a daughter-in-law yet.
-Come on.

514
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,280
You will be soon.

515
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:07,120
-Yeah.
-Right?

516
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:10,400
What’s the name of this village again,
Uncle Headman?

517
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,920
The old name is outdated.

518
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:15,520
Besides,

519
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:17,040
our products

520
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,760
are about to go nationwide.

521
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,560
So we changed the name to...

522
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:24,680
Village 918.

523
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,040
Do you all agree?

524
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:29,640
-Agree.
-Okay, right? Yeah.

525
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:31,120
-Yes, Headman.
-Come.

526
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,520
Let me tie it for you, kid.

527
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,800
Long life and good fortune.

528
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:39,280
Now that you’re here,

529
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:42,600
may you have happiness and prosperity,

530
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:45,240
and be loved by everyone.

531
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:46,560
Bless you.

532
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,720
Come on.

533
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:51,200
Come in.

534
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,320
-Come in.
-Live in peace and happiness.

535
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:54,840
Do you have a longer string?

536
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,400
-Welcome gift.
-Yeah.

537
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:00,600
Here, share it.

538
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:04,320
Here, share it.

539
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:07,720
Sis,

540
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,800
you can stop smiling now.

541
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:12,640
-Your cheeks are about to burst.
-It’s just...

542
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,880
I’m happy.

543
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:17,880
You’re happy,

544
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:20,640
I’m happy too.

545
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,520
Want another drink?

546
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:25,040
Go for it.

547
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:33,840
This jar,

548
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:36,280
it’s on me.

549
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,800
Sis,

550
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:50,920
add some ice too.

551
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,120
Here we go.

552
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:00,400
This whole jar,

553
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:02,480
perfect for the young ones.

554
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:13,520
Hey,

555
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:16,600
I’m not very steady driving, so don’t move too much.

556
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:18,440
Mm.

557
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:21,880
Hold onto me tight and rest your head on my shoulder.

558
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,360
Hurry.

559
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,679
The bike might tip over.

560
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,159
You idiot, you perv.

561
00:34:28,199 --> 00:34:29,920
Get your hand off my chest.

562
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:31,760
-It’s soft.
-Or I’ll kick you off right now.

563
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:34,239
-So soft, so soft.
-You idiot, take it off.

564
